<TITLE> AL, BNP condemn Benazir assassination </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 27 (bdnews24.com)The Awami League and the BNP Thursday condemned the assassination of former Pakistani prime minister Benazir Bhutto. Acting Awami League president Zillur Rahman said the attack was "barbaric". "The attackers are the enemies of humanity," Zillur told bdnews24.com by phone. Senior BNP leader M Saifur Rahman said he was "speechless". BNP leaders Hafiz Uddin Ahmed and Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan separately in a statement said the attackers were against democracy. Khandaker Delwar Hossain, known as a loyalist to detained BNP chief Khaleda Zia, said such an attack was unexpected in a civilised society. bdnews24.c
